<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
The hand written script (verified by J. Rzedowski, per. comm., also see 
<bibRefCitation author="Rzedowski, J" journalOrPublisher="Acta Cientifica Potosina" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" pagination="99 - 121" refId="B21" refString="Rzedowski, J, 1959. Las colecciones botanicas de Wilhelm (Jose Guillermo) Schaffner en San Luis Potosi. I. Acta Cientifica Potosina 3: 99 - 121" title="Las colecciones botanicas de Wilhelm (Jose Guillermo) Schaffner en San Luis Potosi. I." volume="3" year="1959">Rzedowski 1959</bibRefCitation>
) on the label of the holotype (K) says: &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Müehlenbergia">Mueehlenbergia</normalizedToken>
gracilis mihi
</emphasis>
&quot;, indicating that Jose Guillermo Schaffner thought he had collected a new species of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Muhlenbergia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bentham, G" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" refId="B2" refString="Bentham, G, 1882. Plate 1378. Schaffnera gracilis, Benth. Gramineae, Tribe Zoysieae? Hooker's Icones Plantarum 14: 59." title="Plate 1378. Schaffnera gracilis, Benth. Gramineae, Tribe Zoysieae? Hooker's Icones Plantarum 14: 59." year="1882">Bentham (1882)</bibRefCitation>
agreed with Schaffner that it was a new species but thought it had enough unique morphological features (spatheolate sheathed panicles, sessile spikelets and 3(5)-awned upper glumes) to warrant description of a new genus.
</paragraph>
